notesStmt.note: Oxidation of ink throughout, but text is legible.

msContents.summary: 17th-century copy of 71 instructions, dispatches, and letters dated between August 1555 and March 1563.

msItem.title: Instruttioni e lettere dell' illustrissimo et reverendissimo signore Don Carlo Cardinale Carafa, nipote di Papa Paolo IV, concernenti le controversie e li dispareri con la corona di Spagna cioè Filippo II e Carlo V con il sudetto pontifice massimo
msItem.author: Carafa, Carlo, ca. 1517-1561

supportDesc.extent: 140 leaves : 257 x 184 (210 x 122) mm. bound to 263 x 180 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (contemporary paper) + 139 + i (contemporary paper); [i], 1-137, [138]; contemporary foliation in ink, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand.

origin.p: Written in Italy in the first half of the 17th century (Zacour-Hirsch).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Cardinal Antonio Saverio Gentili (ownership stamp on title page).
